enhanced_by.reason: The bufferUp() method ensures that the buffer is filled and up-to-date before consuming characters, which is crucial for the consumeTo() method to function correctly.
The nextIndexOf(char) method is called to find the next occurrence of the delimiter, which is necessary before consuming characters to that delimiter.
Both consumeTo(char) and consumeToEnd() methods handle the consumption of characters, making assertions about the consumed string more robust.
The cacheString method is used to cache the consumed string, which can be used to assert the correctness of the consumed string in consumeTo(char).
